cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AI 

The paper involves the use of machine learning and pattern mining for automated diagnosis and triaging of performance issues in large scale cloud services. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the focus on machine learning and the use of large volumes of service logs, cs.LG and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the integration of the tool into DevOps processes, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE.
